<br>
We over on RZ would like to keep em personally if only on our server(we'll except for the naked loser gankers).<br>
<br>
I think the idea of getting trained then nuked by some loser and losing a velious quest bp would leave something of a bad taste in my mouth.<br>
<br>
As it stands a lot of high end items that represent a huge time investment to get are no drop to limit twinkage which suits RZ just fine as its insane to make items like those losable in so trivial a fashion.<br>
<br>
A better solution would be to remove item loot from RZ entirely since its a broken concept anyway.  The idea of item loot is to add an element of risk to pvp combat which it does BUT its broken in a bunch of ways.  On the whole while it provides risk (more for some than others and mostly in the wrong situations)  it doesn't reward good pvpers and punish poor ones.<br>
<br>
-At the very highest end there is a ton of no drop making pvp for people uber enough risk free.<br>
<br>
-If your a caster you may be disadvantaged in real pvp situations by going naked BUT you should still be able to get kills in many situations especially if you exploit, use hacks, train, or mostly attack people while they are fighting.  As an example of how this works one of the worst pvpers I have ever met (she dies daily and repeatedly)  is auctioning for the tormax piercer for her 20 something alt.  Another example a pk druid I know killed a wounded pally for dw legs and was killed after.  His death should have cost him as much as his win.  A single person attacking 6 damn well should be no matter how wounded 1 member of the 6 may be. It would make lameness less than profitable.  As it stands now he can pvp with a lack of skill that is staggering die 20 times for every kill he manages to get and come out way ahead.<br>
<br>
-A 3rd factor, people don't lose good stuff in most real pvp situations because they can bag or choose not to risk the gear in the first place.  A large part of the loss that is supposed to provide the risk factor for pvp is primary present in exp groups that get ganked.<br>
<br>
In essence current item loot makes it risky to wear your gear while doing pve things, finances endless twinking by people who play one char only to get cheap ass kills then log to their &quot;good&quot; char, and generally makes all classes fight at less than their full potential in pvp except the ubers.<br>
<br>
Given a choice I would vote for a SZ style exp bonus and penalty for death.<br>
<br>
Looking at that carefully almost everyone would gain exp wise from this.  The small amount of unrezed pvp deaths wouldn't touch the exp you would gain from the bonus.<br>
<br>
<br>
